This may be implicit, but I'd like to help out other people that have faced this bug through `Files` (`Nautilus`), since the error message varies a bit, and it may be hard to find or search for it online.

This bug is reproducible by trying to copy several files (like a photo library) to Google Drive through `Files`.

Error message (with some text redacted):
```
Error while copying "filename.extension".

There was an error copying the file into google-drive://username@...
tlsALPHANUMERIC-TOKEN.

Authentication required: {
 "error": {
  "errors": [
   {
    "domain": "global",
    "reason": "authError",
    "message": "Invalid Credentials",
    "locationType": "header",
    "location": "Authorization"
   }
  ],
  "code": 401,
  "message": "Invalid Credentials"
 }
}

```

I looked at the code, at it fails to extract the IP address from the gui elements:
```rust
 87       connect_button.connect_clicked(move |_| {
 88             let active_row = devices_listbox.get_selected_row().unwrap();
 89 
 90             // Very hackish way to get the selected ip address
 91             let box1: gtk::Box = active_row.get_children()[0].clone().downcast().unwrap();
 92             let box2: gtk::Box = box1.get_children()[1].clone().downcast().unwrap();
 93             let ip_label: gtk::Label = box2.get_children()[1].clone().downcast().unwrap();
 94             let ip_addr: IpAddr = IpAddr::from_str(ip_label.get_text().unwrap().              to_string().as_str()).unwrap();
 95 
 96             // Get GCastDevice
 97             let device = gcd.get_device_by_ip_addr(ip_addr).unwrap();
 98             sender.send(Action::PlaybackConnectGCastDevice(device)).unwrap();
 99             widget.set_visible(false);
100             widget.hide();
101         });
```

Is this triggered by having multiple Chromecast units available?

